<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Beijing Examines Designs Works For National Theater </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Beijing Municipal People's
Government has received 44 designs for the National Grand Theater
and will plan to solicit opinions from the general public.
</P>
<P>
Wang Siquan, director of the trans-century project, said the
designs were submitted by 36 architectural institutes, including
20 foreign firms.
</P>
<P>
Their designs will be exhibited in the Museum of Chinese
Revolution between July 19-27. An 11-member appraisal committee
headed by Wu Liangyong will examine the designs and select the
final three candidates.
</P>
<P>
Wu is a professor at Qinghua University and academician with
the Chinese Academy of Sciences and Chinese Academy of Engineering.
</P>
<P>
Wan said the designs must meet the following three requirements
-- modern architectural style and interior decoration, appease the
tastes of the general public in China, and blend with nearby
Tiananmen Square.
</P>
<P>
The theater complex, located on the west side of the Great Hall
of the People at downtown Beijing's Tiananmen Square, will include
four major facilities -- the opera theater, concert hall, drama
theater and performance center. The project will be completed at
estimated cost of 3.54 billion yuan (about 420 million US dollars).
</P>
</TEXT>
