<HEADLINE> Yangtze Navigation Suspension Continues </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YICHANG, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The suspension of navigation in
the Yangtze Three Gorges area continues due to surging flood
waters.
</P>
<P>
However, various forms of transportation has been used to
disperse the over 46,000 passengers stranded over the past three
days.
</P>
<P>
Both the temporary lock and water diversion channel at the
Three Gorges Dam were closed between July 10-11 as a result of the
record flood peak of 50,000 cu.m. per second.
</P>
<P>
Yichang transportation departments provided over 1,800 buses
to transport stranded passengers to new railway, air, ship and bus
connections during the period.
</P>
<P>
Hydrological and meteorological forecasts indicate that the
water flow rate of 50,000 cu.m. per second will remain until July
20 and navigation will remain temporarily suspended.  
</P>
</TEXT>
