<HEADLINE> Central Govt Assists HK in Air Cargo Handling </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Central Government, at the
request of the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region Government
(HKSARG), would render every possible assistance to help relieve
the cargo handling problems encountered by the new airport, Chief
Executive Tung Chee Hwa said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The HKSARG said in a press release that it sent a letter to the
Central Government Monday, briefing them on the latest position
regarding the air cargo handling operation at the new airport. A
request was made to the relevant authorities to facilitate the
airlines concerned in using the Huangtian Airport at Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
A joint departmental meeting was held Tuesday morning by the
Central Government. Attending the meeting were officials from the
civil aviation, customs, inspection of commodities authorities and
the administration. The meeting agreed to offer full support and
assistance to the SAR government in its cargo handling services.
</P>
<P>
A delegation headed by Deputy Director of the Hong Kong and
Macao Affairs Office of the State Council Chen Zuo'er, is to
arrive in Shenzhen Tuesday night and will meet on Wednesday
morning with a delegation of HKSARG led by Secretary for Economic
Services Stephen Ip.
</P>
<P>
Tung said: "On behalf of the SARG and the Hong Kong people, I
would like to express my deepest gratitude to the Central
Government for its concern and support."
</P>
<P>
"I believe that with the assistance of the Central Government,
the air cargo shipment problems faced by our importers and
exporters will be greatly relieved," the chief executive noted.
</P>
<P>
According to the Airport Authority, approximately one third of
Hong Kong's normal daily air cargo volume moved through the Hong
Kong International Airport at Chek Lap Kok on Tuesday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
