<HEADLINE> Mountain Torrent Destroys Lanzhou-Xinjiang Railway Line </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, July 14 (Xinhua) -- A 42-km section of the
Lanzhou-Xinjiang Railway linking Gansu Province and the Xinjiang
Uygur Autonomous Region in northwest China was destroyed by a
mountain torrent on Monday and is currently under repair.
</P>
<P>
A mountain torrent hit the double-track line between
Shisanjianfang and Liaodun at 07:00 on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Some 1,287 passengers aboard one passenger train and 63 freight
and passenger trains were stranded in nine hours between 12:00
Monday and 09:00 this morning.
</P>
<P>
Over 1,000 rescue workers have worked on the project for 26
hours and repair efforts are progressing smoothly.  
</P>
</TEXT>
