<HEADLINE> Chinese Taipei Bowler Wins Hong Kong Masters Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Ku Hui Chin from
Chinese Taipei won the women's title at the Hong Kong Bowling
Masters Cup, the third stop of this year's Asian Bowling Tour,
here on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Ku, 24, a university student with playing experience of four
years, had won the trios and five-player titles at the 15th Far
East Bowling Championships here earlier this month.
</P>
<P>
Ku, who beat teammate and winner of four gold medals at the Far
East championships Tseng Su Fen 195-186 in the semi-final earlier
in the day, went on to get the title with a 192-164 win over Karen
Lorenzana of hosts Hong Kong, China.
</P>
<P>
Lorenzana, third placer in the women's doubles at the Far East
tournament, won over Singapore's third-seeded Jesmine Ho,
silver-medalist at the 1995 World Cup, in the semi-finals. 
</P>
</TEXT>
