<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambican President to Attend Summit in Cape </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican President Joaquim
Chissano will leave for Praia, capital of Cape Verde Wednesday to
attend the second summit of the Community of Portuguese-Speaking
Countries scheduled on July 16 to 17.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, according to the news communique issued here
Tuesday, will discuss cooperation between countries in the
Community, and is expected to sign cooperation agreement on
education, immigrants.
</P>
<P>
The situation in Guinea Bissau will also be one of the major
issues during the meeting. The month-long armed conflict in the
west African country has caused the deaths of several hundred
people.
</P>
<P>
Senior officials from the Community held an expert meeting in
Praia Monday. The two-day meeting of foreign ministers started
Tuesday to make preparations for the summit.
</P>
<P>
Chissano will be accompanied by Eneas Comiche, Minister of
Economic and Social Affairs, and Leonardo Simao, Minister of
Foreign Affairs and Co-operation.
</P>
<P>
The first summit of the Community of Portuguese Speaking
Countries was held in July, 1996 in Lisbon, capital of Portugal,
which marked the founding of the Community. 
</P>
</TEXT>
