<HEADLINE> Greek Air Force Plane Goes Off Runway </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 14 (Xinhua) -- A Greek Air Force A-7 corsair jet
went off the runway at the western Agrinio airport while making an
emergency landing after the discovery of a problem in the fuel
supply system.
</P>
<P>
The plane, which had taken off from Araxos air base and being
on a training flight, was out of control and went off the runway
because a problem with the braking system, but the two pilots were
not hurt, the semi-official Athens News Agency (ANA) reported.
</P>
