<HEADLINE> Arafat to Arrive in Pakistan for Brief Visit </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, July 14 (Xinhua) -- President of the Palestine State
Yasser Arafat will arrive here from Beijing Wednesday for a brief
visit to Pakistan, the News Network International (NNI) said
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
During his stay here, Arafat is expected to have a meeting with
Pakistani Prime Minister Nawaz Sharif.
</P>
<P>
The two leaders will discuss matters of mutual interest,
particularly the current situation in South Asia, according to the
NNI.
</P>
<P>
Sharif will brief Arafat on Pakistan's rationale for its
nuclear option and the tension in the region after nuclear
explosions by India and Pakistan in May.
</P>
<P>
Talking to the media on Monday during a stopover here on his
way to China, Arafat stressed the need for a peaceful and
negotiated settlement of the issue of Kashmir and other issues
between Pakistan and India.
</P>
<P>
He also expressed the hope that the upcoming meeting between
Sharif and his Indian counterpart Atal Bihari Vajpayee, scheduled
for late this month in Colombo, Sri Lanka, would be fruitful.
</P>
</TEXT>
