<HEADLINE> Tehran Stock Exchange Index Falls Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The general price index at Tehran
Stock Exchange fell sharply again on Tuesday to 1,581.10 points,
down by 8.36 points compared to that on Monday.
</P>
<P>
It was the second time within two weeks that the index dropped
by more than five points. On July 5, the index fell by 11.95
points.
</P>
<P>
A total of 1,069,291 shares worth over 4.35 billion rials
(about 790,000 U.S. dollars) exchanged hands in 804 turns for 354
applicants. The shares of 12 companies made gains while those of
11 others declined.
</P>
<P>
Experts believed that the main reason behind the fall was the
failure of companies to inject fresh capitals as a result of the
country's current economic problems caused by oil price
fall. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
