<HEADLINE> Greece to Create More Jobs for Young People </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ATHENS, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Greece plans to create more jobs
for young men in the next few years as part of its efforts to deal
with the country's unemployment problem.
</P>
<P>
Greece's Labor and Social Security Minister Miltiades
Papaioannou said Tuesday that the Greek government was
particularly concerned about the high level of youth unemployment
and planned to create jobs for 200,000 young people in the next
three years.
</P>
<P>
He added that a third of those new positions would be created
by the end of this year, 50,000 jobs would be devoted to the
unemployed between the ages of 20 and 27.
</P>
<P>
Greece's jobless rate currently stands at 10.3 percent.
