<HEADLINE> U.N. Urged to Support ECOWAS Efforts in Guinea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of African
Unity (OAU) has urged the U.N. Security Council to give its full
support to the Economic Community of West African States (ECOWAS)
in its efforts to ensure the return of constitutional legality in
Guinea Bissau.
</P>
<P>
According to an OAU press release issued here Tuesday, the
call was contained in a communique issued at the end of the 49th
ordinary session of the central organ at ambassadorial level here
Monday.
</P>
<P>
After considering the report on the mission of the special
envoy of the OAU secretary-general to Guinea Bissau, said the
communique, the central organ endorsed the decisions and
recommendations of the joint meeting of ECOWAS foreign and
defense ministers held in Abidjan on July 3.
</P>
<P>
The central organ reaffirmed OAU's strong and unequivocal
condemnation of the mutiny in Guinea Bissau perpetrated against
the democratically elected government of President Joao Bemardo
Viera and called upon all member states and the international
community to refrain from giving any form of support to the
authors of the mutiny.
</P>
<P>
The central organ expressed its support for Guinea and Senegal
as well as for the ECOWAS member states for their involvement on
the side of the constitutional authorities of Guinea Bissau upon
request by the latter.
</P>
<P>
It called for the search of a lasting solution based on dialog
and other relevant measures adopted by ECOWAS with a view to
restoring peace and the authority of the legal government
throughout the country.
</P>
<P>
The central organ also appealed to the international community
to provide all the necessary humanitarian assistance in
collaboration with the authorities of Guinea Bissau and the
countries hosting the refugees. 
</P>
</TEXT>
