<HEADLINE> Ford Belgium to Retrieve As Many As 11,000 Cars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRUSSELS, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Ford Belgium announced on Tuesday
its plan to retrieve 11,000 cars for possible problems with
passenger airbags.
</P>
<P>
The Belgian affiliate of the United States carmaking giant said
that the airbags sometimes deploy without any reason and the
problems were feared to be caused by static electricity in the
car.
</P>
<P>
The cars to be retrieved in Belgium are of three models, Ford
Escort, Ford Mondeo and Ford Scorpio, manufactured between March
1997 and March this year.
</P>
<P>
Ford Belgium stressed that the move was of a preventive nature.
</P>
<P>
On Monday, however, Ford Werke, a German affiliate of Ford,
announced its plan to retrieve up to 124,000 cars in Germany.
</P>
<P>
A total of 21 airbags have mis-deployed since last year and one
passenger suffered light injuries, according to German sources.
</P>
</TEXT>
