<HEADLINE> Yeltsin Meets with Duma Leaders </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Russian President Boris Yeltsin on
Tuesday called on Duma's leaders to adopt the bills facilitating
implementation of the stabilization program.
</P>
<P>
According to the Itar-Tass news agency, during the meeting with
Duma's leaders in the Kremlin Yeltsin said "We need the
stabilization program not only for the sake of implementation. We
will not be able to implement it unless you approve (the bills)."
</P>
<P>
Both the president and the State Duma are opposed to the
creation of unconstitutional bodies of power in Russia, Duma
speaker Gennady Seleanyov told a press conference after the
meeting with Yeltsin.
</P>
<P>
He said the president was told that the State Duma would
categorically oppose "any unconstitutional bodies of power, like a
State Council proposed by the "oligarchs" after their meeting with
the government.
</P>
<P>
At the meeting Yeltsin proposed that the status of roundtable
meetings of representatives of all branches of power under the
president be upgraded, president's spokesman Sergei Yastrzhembsky
said.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the State Duma's leadership suggested that such
meetings become regular and that roundtable sessions be resumed in
the fall.
</P>
<P>
Duma deputies, on the whole, favor "concerted efforts" for
stabilizing the situation in the country. They proposed that a
trilateral commission for preparation of draft laws be created
with the participation of members of the Duma, the Federation
Council and the Cabinet, the spokesman said.  
</P>
