<HEADLINE> 6 Bodies of Crashed Ukrainian Plane Crew Recovered </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Six bodies of the Ukrainian
cargo plane that plunged into the sea last night soon after
take-off from the United Arab Emirates have been recovered by the
coastal and border guards.
</P>
<P>
The remaining two of the eight crew members on board the plane
when it crashed were still missing and feared dead. The search was
continuing for them and the instruments that recorded flight
condition and data.
</P>
<P>
According to Sheikh Salem Al-Kasemi, chief of Ras Al-Khaimah
International Airport, the coastal guards recovered four bodies of
the crew by 10:00 local time (0600 GMT). Another two bodies were
found in the afternoon.
</P>
<P>
The tragic incident took place Monday soon after the Ilyushin
76, leased by a Kiev-based private air company, took off for
Mykolayiv, Ukraine. The plane crashed about 500 meters offshore.
</P>
<P>
Carrying 44 tons of ordinary cargo loaded Monday evening, it
took off at 23:12 local time (1912 GMT) from runway No. 34 of Ras
Al-Khaimah Airport, some 300 kilometers northeast of the
capital.
</P>
<P>
The take-off process went smoothly without any abnormality.
</P>
<P>
Eyewitnesses have reported that the four-engine plane caught
fire and exploded before crashing into the sea. 
</P>
</TEXT>
