<HEADLINE> 26 Kurdish Rebels Killed in Southeastern Turkey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- A total of 26 members of the
outlawed Kurdish Workers' Party (PKK) were killed in recent
military operations by Turkish government troops in southeastern
Turkey, the Anatolia News Agency reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The fighting took place in the southeastern provinces of Van,
Bingol, Tunceli, Hakkari, Diyarbakir as well as Sirnak. One
soldier was also killed and seven others wounded.
