In a separate incident, a group of PKK militants raided a
villiage in the eastern province of Erzurum Monday night, killing
five civilians, including one village guard.
</P>
<P>
The PKK has been fighting the Turkish government since 1984 in
an attempt to establish an independent Kurdish state in
southeastern Turkey. More than 35,000 people have been killed in
the armed clashes. 
