charter out new areas of cooperation between the two countries
and curb the large trade deficit Kenya runs with India.
</P>
<P>
Kenya exports to India grew by 49 percent to 22 million U.S.
Dollars in the 1996/97 year while exports from India dropped from
a peak of 250 million Dollars in 1995/1996 to about 180 million
Dollars.
</P>
<P>
"India is one of Kenya's leading trading and investment
partners" while Kenya remains the gateway for India to the rising
markets in east African and the Great Lakes region, said Godana.
</P>
<P>
He also called on about 100,000 people of Indian origin in
Kenya to "consolidate their investments in an effort to boost
exports to India."
</P>
<P>
Earlier, Indian Ambassador R.K. Bhatia said that the Indian
government is planning to take some new initiatives to enhance
bilateral relations especially in the economic field.
</P>
<P>
As a part, a display of India's technological prowess is in
the offing as India Tech'98 will hit Nairobi in August with up to
100 companies mainly in engineering and information technology
sectors expected to participate in. 
