administrations in the UNITA-controlled areas, and work closely
with the government to settle all the problems left unresolved in
the 1994 Lusaka Peace Protocol.
</P>
<P>
The leaders agreed to join efforts in persuading Savimbi to
refrain from endangering peace, security and stability in the
three neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
Dialog is the only way to peace, and war can only lead to the
killings of innocent civilians and the destruction of Angols's
infrastructure, the three leaders said in the statement.
</P>
