<HEADLINE> Privatization Program Half Fulfilled in Romania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The privatization developed at
snail's pace in the first half of the year, reported Tuesday the
daily Adevarul (The Truth), quoting data of the State Ownership
Fund, which is in charge of the privatization process.
</P>
<P>
As many as 2,800 commercial companies are included in the 1998
privatization program, of which 1,200 are to effectively be sold
by the end of 1998, but in the first half of the year, only 304
sale-purchase contracts were signed. So, the privatization program
on the first six months of 1998 was only 50 percent fulfilled.
</P>
<P>
The reason that kept the foreign investors away from Romania
was, according to Privatization Minister Sorin Dimitriu, "first of
all the wreaking effects of the political crisis at end-1997 and
the beginning of 1998." Inadequate legislations and bureaucracy
are among the other hindrances in attracting the foreign
investors.
</P>
<P>
Data of the State Ownership Fund showed that the general stage
of privatization till July 10, 1998 is as follows: 4,647 companies
turned private, out of which 3,465 are small, 1,015 medium-sized
and 167 large. As many as 517 contracts were drawn back. 
</P>
</TEXT>
