<HEADLINE> S. Africa, Mozambique to Have One-Stop Border </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 14 (Xinhua) -- South Africa and Mozambique
Tuesday signed an agreement to establish a one-stop border post
facility at the Ressano Garcia/Lebombo border post, South African
Press Association (SAPA) reported.
</P>
<P>
The move, prompted by dramatic increases in road, rail and
pedestrian traffic between the two countries, will result in the
upgrading of the Lebombo border control facility, SAPA said.
</P>
<P>
The project will take an estimated 24 months to complete.
</P>
<P>
It is expected to be South Africa's gateway to the Maputo
Development Corridor, which is believed to be the largest
infrastructure project on the African continent.
</P>
<P>
The agreement was signed in Maputo by South African Public
Works Minister Jeff Radebe and his Mozambican counterpart,
Roberto Costley-White. 
</P>
