<P>
JERUSALEM -- Ten Palestinians were injured Wednesday in fierce
clashes with Israeli soldiers in Rashaydeh town, south of
Bethlehem, the Voice of Palestine radio reported.
</P>
<P>
The clashes occurred when the Israeli soldiers raided the
town, imposing a military siege around it and started to
confiscate herds belonging to the Palestinians, the radio said.
</P>
<P>
The Palestinians resisted against the confiscation and clashed
with the Israeli soldiers, who fired rubber bullets at the
palestinians.
</P>
<P>
Among the injured, five have been sent to a hospital in
Bethlehem.
</P>
<P>
Israeli army said that during the clashes, only five
Palestinians were injured by the rubber bullets, Israel Radio
said. (Israel-Clash)
