<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lanka's Elections Commissioner
Dayananda De Silva announced Wednesday that elections will be held
on August 28 this year for five provincial councils.
</P>
<P>
The elections should have been held before the terms of the
existing five provincial councils expired in June this year. The
five provinces are Western Province, Central Province, North
Central Province, Uva and Sabaragamuwa.
