<HEADLINE> Destroyed Lanzhou-Xinjiang Railway Line Under Intensive Repair </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
URUMQI, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Intensive repairs on a section of
northwest China's Lanzhou-Xinjiang Railway Line damaged by
mountain torrents on Monday are underway.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,000 railroad workers are now engaged in the repair
project, according to China Central Television Station (CCTV).
</P>
<P>
Workers face a difficult task due to the complicated terrain in
the region. Nonetheless, the line is expected to open to traffic
by midnight on July 16, according to reports by CCTV.
</P>
<P>
Transportation, food and lodging arrangements have been made
for more than 8,000 passengers stranded at the Lanzhou Railway
Station.
</P>
<P>
The double-track Lanzhou-Xinjiang Railway links Gansu Province
and the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region, with the damaged section
stretching 42 km between Shisanjianfang and Liaodun.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
