<HEADLINE> UK Still Favorite for Asian Investment in Europe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Britain enjoyed an all-time record
number of inward investment projects during the last year,
according to the Invest in Britain Bureau (IBB), Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
IBB reported 618 foreign direct investment projects from
throughout the world -- the first time the number has ever
exceeded 500.
</P>
<P>
A total of 45,937 new jobs were created during the 1997/98 year
as a direct result of overseas-sourced investment, with another
78,685 jobs safeguarded, IBB said.
</P>
<P>
Launching the organization's Annual Review of Operations 1998,
President of the Board of Trade Margaret Beckett said it was due
to the Government's "deep continuing commitment to economic
stability, improved international competitiveness and
determination to establish a new sense of partnership throughout
industry and the investment network."
</P>
<P>
Commenting on the effects of Asian economic difficulties during
the year, Andrew Fraser, IBB's Chief Executive said: "We are
watching the situation carefully ... However, we are confident the
region's companies will be back on the European investment scene
in due course." 
</P>
</TEXT>
