<HEADLINE> Expert Group Set up on HK Sewage Disposal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 15 (Xinhua) -- An expert group on sewage
disposal will be set up to take forward discussions between Hong
Kong and the mainland on options for Hong Kong's Strategic Sewage
Disposal Scheme (SSDS).
</P>
<P>
The expert group, comprising officials and experts from both
sides, will meet for the first time here on Thursday, according to
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region government.
</P>
<P>
The group will enable the mainland and Hong Kong to exchange
information and ideas on the scheme and seek common views on the
future planning of the system for the protection of coastal
waters.
</P>
<P>
Before the handover, discussion on issues related to the scheme
used to be carried out at the then Expert Group on Sewage Disposal
of the Sino-British Joint Liaison Group (JLG). Since it had
completed its assigned duties in June 1997, the work of the JLG
expert group was concluded, as was the involvement of the JLG in
this issue.  
</P>
