<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Chen Zuo'er, deputy director of
the State Council's Hong Kong and Macao Affairs Office, has
pledged that related central and local departments will fully
support the new Hong Kong airport by handling air cargo at the
Huangtian Airport in neighboring Shenzhen.
</P>
<P>
The pledge came during a Tuesday meeting attended by officials
from the civil aviation, customs, inspection of commodities
departments of the central government and their counterparts from
the Hong Kong Special Administrative Region (HKSAR).
</P>
<P>
The two sides agreed that cargo planes operated by overseas air
carriers will be allowed to use the Huangtian Airport, and all
cargoes will be transported between the city and the region in the
most expeditious manner.
</P>
<P>
They pledged complete preparations to service arrivals and
departures by early Saturday morning.
</P>
<P>
The Huangtian Airport, which has a parking apron covering
290,000 sq.m., can service 10 Boeing 747 aircraft and a warehouse
with a capacity to store cargoes carried by six aircraft.
