<HEADLINE> Local Official Convicted For Malfeasance </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The People's Intermediate Court
in Wenzhou, east China's Zhejiang Province, recently sentenced a
local official to 13 years of imprisonment for accepting bribes to
assign individuals to official posts.
</P>
<P>
Tong Genshun, former head of the organization department of the
Pingyang County Party Committee was convicted of accepting
separate brides totalling 150,000 yuan (about 18,000 U.S. dollars)
plus 800 U.S. dollars. The local committee also expelled Tong from
the Communist Party of China.
</P>
<P>
Tong's case involved several dozen people, the vast majority of
whom ranked as department officials at the county level. Individuals
paying bribes for promotions have also received punishment,
including removal from the posts they bought and expulsion from the
Party. 
</P>
</TEXT>
