<HEADLINE> Fire Kills 7 Prisoners, Injures 2 in Iran </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 15 (Xinhua) -- A fire killed seven prisoners and
injured two others in the prison of Mashhad, northeastern province
of Khorasan, an Iranian judicial official revealed here on
Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to official news agency IRNA, the official, whose name
was not given, said the incident happened on Tuesday and the fire
started from a carpentry workshop inside the prison and spread
over several cells.
</P>
<P>
Some 100 million rials (about 18,000 U.S. dollars) in damage
has been inflicted on the prison installations, the official said,
investigations are now underway to find the cause of fire.
</P>
<P>
It is said that the fire broke out when an inmate threw his
cigarette butt at the inflammable materials inside the workshop,
IRNA added. 
