<HEADLINE> 30 Die of Unknown Reason in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Thirty people have died of unknown
cause in the past 30 days in Manila and police authorities have
sought the help of the Department of Health, the Philippine News
Agency reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The report said the victims are varied professionals, of
different ages but mostly male and did not manifest any sign of
violence. They were suspected by the police to have died of
nightmare or distress.
</P>
<P>
Senior Inspector Pete Campano, chief of the Western Police
District Homicide Division, was quoted as saying that the police
believed that the deaths were caused by nightmare or distress, but
did not know how to stop the rising threat.
</P>
<P>
"We have our medico-legal officers to do this -- determination
of death -- but we have no means or know-how to advise people on
how to curb it," he said.
</P>
<P>
Campano urged officials of the Department of Health to take
concern over the situation and help them advise people on what to
do to avoid the deaths.
</P>
<P>
The latest victim was a 29-year-old security guard who was
found lifeless with no sign of violence or foul play inside the
room he rented, Campano said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
