<HEADLINE> Jordan's Stock Market Closes Slightly Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
AMMAN, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Price index in market value on the
Amman Financial Market (AFM) closed at 178.82 points Wednesday,
2.75 points higher than Tuesday, the AFM daily report said.
</P>
<P>
Total value of trading on Wednesday reached 9,191,576
Jordanian dinars (12,982,451 U.S. dollars), according to the
report.
</P>
<P>
Also for Wednesday, the number of turned-over shares reached
864,530 and that of carried-out contracts 657, the report said.
</P>
</TEXT>
