<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuwait Stock Exchange Index up 47.7 Points </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Kuwait Stock Exchange index
jumped 47.7 points Wednesday to close at 2,127.3 points, a 22.9
percent rise compared with Tuesday's closing.
</P>
<P>
The volume, transactions and value all took a sharp increase
with a total of 130.91 million shares over 3,231 deals against
85.81 million shares over 1,928 deals Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The value of shares changed hands also hiked from Tuesday's
14.60 million Kuwaiti dinars (48.18 million U.S. dollars) to
25.43 million Kuwaiti dinars (83.91 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Kuwait Stock Exchange index dropped to 1,996.8 points last
Saturday, the first time sliding below the 2,000-point level this
year.
</P>
<P>
The market bounced back Sunday, edging up 38.6 points,
followed by a moderate 14.4-point rise Monday and a 29.8-point up
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Market analysts said a government plan to postpone debt
payment by Kuwaitis helped the bourse's consecutive regain.
</P>
<P>
They said like in the past three days, continued official talk
of a rescue package to tackle Kuwait's economic woes, caused by
weak oil prices, also contributed to the upward trend. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
