<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Overseas Investment In Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Shanghai utilized 2.86 billion
U.S. dollars in overseas investment in the first half of this
year, up 26 percent from the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The increase is mainly attributed to official approval of a
stainless steel project funded by Germany's Krupp and Thyssen,
which involves 1.26 billion U.S. dollars in investment.
</P>
<P>
Shanghai approved 110 overseas-funded projects in the
January-June period, half of which are industrial projects, and 43
percent of which are in the Pudong Area.
</P>
<P>
Paid-in investment amounted to 1.25 billion U.S. dollars in
that period, down 15.3 percent from the corresponding period of
last year. Shanghai expects paid-in overseas investment to amount
to 4 billion U.S. dollars this year.
</P>
<P>
The city's Mayor Xu Kuangdi says that they need to improve the
investment environment to make it an ideal place for overseas
capital. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
