<HEADLINE> Beijing Cartoon Museum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Beijing, China's capital, is
planning to open a cartoon museum by the end of this year.
</P>
<P>
The 3,000-sq.m. museum will be in Beijing Children's Palace
near the city's center and will have a display of several hundred
cartoons from the 70-year history of the art form in China.
</P>
<P>
Chinese are quite familiar with various types of cartoons like
movies, in book form, on TV, and in advertisements.
</P>
<P>
They love foreign cartoons as well as those traditional Chinese
forms like puppets, paper-cuts, and leather-silhouette shows.
</P>
<P>
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
