<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Australian Parliamentary Report Denounces Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CANBERRA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Israel's approach to the Middle
East peace process was denounced here Wednesday as short-sighted
and a tragedy in an Australian parliamentary report just four
weeks before a visit to Australia by Israeli Prime Minister
Benjamin Netanyahu.
</P>
<P>
The report was released by the Australian parliamentary
delegation led by Ian Sinclair, speaker of Australian House of
Representatives following their recent visit to Syria, Lebanon,
Jordan and Israel.
</P>
<P>
"The delegation concluded that the current position adopted by
the Israeli government on the peace process is very
short-sighted," the report said.
</P>
<P>
"The delegation is of the view that the peace process has
entered a critical period which demands timely action.
</P>
<P>
"The response of the Netanyahu government, however, suggests it
has concluded that delay is to Israel's advantage."
</P>
<P>
The report warned Israel was placing its future at risk by
stalling the peace process and puts pressure on Australian Prime
Minister John Howard ahead of his meeting with Netanyahu next
month in Australia.
</P>
<P>
"The delegation welcomes the prospect of a visit to Australia
by Prime Minister Netanyahu because it would give another
opportunity to express the strong view of the parliament,
government and people of Australia that an early settlement is
essential and that the present stance of the Israeli government is
not contributing to the achievement of that goal," the report
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
