<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Tax Official In Tianjin Given Life Sentence </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIANJIN, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The No. 2 Intermediate People's
Court of Tianjin Municipality has sentenced a local tax official to
life in prison for embezzlement and corruption.
</P>
<P>
Luo Shuangyin, former deputy director of a branch of the
Municipal Taxation Consulting Office, embezzled 620,000 yuan in
tax payments, and asked enterprises to pay 400,000 yuan in bribes
to avoid taxes.
</P>
<P>
Luo also charged local enterprises service fees as a tax
consultant in his own branch, and pocketed the money.
</P>
<P>
The No.2 Branch of the Municipal People's Procuratorate upheld
the guilty charge on counts of embezzlement and corruption, and
instituted proceedings. The court also deprived Luo of political
rights for life and confiscated 50,000 yuan worth of
illegally-gained property.  
</P>
</TEXT>
