<BODY>
<HEADLINE> World Cup Twice Popular As Winter Olympics on Internet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The official World Cup Internet site
scored 1.7 billion hits, more than double the 680 million for the
winter Olympics in Nagano, Japan at the beginning of the year,
France Telecom said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
This was far higher than the expected one billion hits, with
people from 164 countries visiting the site, France Telecom said.
</P>
<P>
On June 30, the day the second round finished and the
quarter-finalists were known, 74 million people visited the site.
</P>
<P>
The French organizing committee site, put out by France Telecom
and several other partners, had been open since May 6. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980715.0134 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kuala Lumpur Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on the Kuala
Lumpur Stock Exchange closed higher Wednesday in line with strong
performance of regional markets.
</P>
<P>
At the close, the 100-quality stock Composite Index rose 13.21
points, or 3.14 percent, to 433.54, the all share Emas Index added
2.72 points to 108.87, the Industrial Index gained 26.89 points to
892.06 and the second board index rose 0.80 of a point to 93.30.
</P>
<P>
Gainers led losers by 365 to 186, while 149 counters were
unchanged, 223 untraded and 44 suspended.
</P>
<P>
The day's turnover increased to 109.929 million shares worth
208.985 million ringgit (about 50.357 million U.S. dollars) from
Tuesday's 97.347 million shares valued at 174.028 million ringgit
(about 41.934 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
The main board turnover rose to 105.092 million shares valued
at 203.470 million ringgit (about 49.028 million U.S. dollars)
from 92.916 million shares worth 167.582 million ringgit (about
40.381 million U.S. dollars traded on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The second board turnover increased to 4.837 million shares
worth 5.515 million ringgit (about 1.328 million U.S. dollars)
from 4.431 million shares valued at 6.446 million ringgit (about
1.553 million U.S. dollars) on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Off market volume soared to 18.508 million shares valued at
17.618 million ringgit (about 4.245 million U.S. dollars) from
Tuesday's 904,916 shares worth 2.378 million ringgit (about 0.573
million U.S. dollars).
</P>
</TEXT>
