<BODY>
<HEADLINE> India's Industrial Production Grows 4.5 Percent in May </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, July 15 (Xinhua) -- India's index of industrial
production has recorded a 4.5 percent growth in May this year,
according to the figures released here Wednesday by the Central
Statistical Organization (CSO).
</P>
<P>
The country's manufacturing sector, the backbone of industrial
growth, continued its slump registering a 4.4 percent growth rate.
The mining sector showed a negative growth rate of 0.2 percent.
</P>
<P>
The capital goods sector also had a poor performance posting a
near stagnant growth of 0.6 percent. Basic goods and consumer
non-durables clocked in with growth rates of 3.6 percent and 2
percent respectively.
</P>
<P>
As per user-based classification, the growth of intermediate
goods was the highest at 7.8 percent in May, followed by the 7.7
percent growth in the consumer durables, CSO said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
