<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Increased Fixed Assets Input Helping Economic Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, July 15 (Xinhua) -- China's Hebei Province will
increase fixed assets input to guarantee an 11 percent increase
in its GDP this year.
</P>
<P>
Local fixed assets input is expected to increase 19 percent
from the 1997 figure to 170 billion yuan this year and will focus
on basic industries, infrastructure, technological improvements in
state enterprises, hi-tech industries, residential housing, the
electric-power grids in rural areas, state grain storage, and
improving the ecology.
</P>
<P>
The city of Tangshan, a traditional industrial base, has made
an effort on 107 key projects, helping the economy rise 13 percent
during the first half of this year compared with the same period
in 1997.
</P>
<P>
During the first half, local state industrial enterprises and
non-state enterprises with annual sales of more than 5 million
yuan had nearly 127 billion yuan in output, an 11 percent rise
from the same 1997 period, and a production-to-sale ratio rising
0.5 percentage points to 95.7 percent. 
</P>
</TEXT>
