<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Zambia to Export 1,600 Tons of Paprika in 1999 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Zambia will export a total of 1,600
tons of paprika next year to earn the country over 1.5 million
U.S. Dollars in foreign exchange.
</P>
<P>
This was disclosed here Tuesday by Brian Hakamangwe, member of
Zambia Association for High Value Crops responsible for
production and logistics, Times of Zambia reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The association has secured export contracts with South Africa
and India, but could not export the required quota this season
due to limited production capacity, said Hakamangwe.
</P>
<P>
He said that the association which has 1,000 members at
present is recruiting more members to ensure that more
small-scale farmers join the organization to receive paprika
inputs for them to undertake production of the crop this season.
</P>
<P>
The South African market requires 50 tons of paprika from
Zambia monthly while India expects the association to export 800
tons of the crop annually, according to Hakamangwe.
</P>
<P>
This year, the association is expected to export 500 tons of
paprika to the two countries instead of the targeted 2,000 tons.
</P>
<P>
Zambia produces the best quality paprika because of its good
climatic conditions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
