<HEADLINE> Namibia Appeals for International Aid </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Namibia has appealed to the
international community to help finance its drought relief
program, said sources reaching here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Namibian Minister of Agriculture, Water and Rural Development
Helmut Angula said Tuesday after a cabinet meeting that about 12
million U.S. Dollars were needed for the scheme.
</P>
<P>
The Namibian government needed more than six million U.S.
Dollars from the donor community, the rest would come from its
own resources, Angula said.
</P>
<P>
Additional funds would also be required to address water
crisis and finance food-for-work programs, he said, adding that
about 161,000 Namibians needed food aid.
</P>
<P>
Namibia, with a population of 1.6 million, has been hard-hit by
years of drought and bad climate. 
</P>
</TEXT>
