<HEADLINE> China's Information Industry Maintaining Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- China's posts and
telecommunications sector did 111.3 billion yuan in business in
the first half of the year, up 37.7 percent from the same period
last year.
</P>
<P>
Output of electronics products surged 26.2 percent at 224.8
billion yuan up to the end of June.
</P>
<P>
The telecommunication sector's spending on fixed assets came to
50.8 billion yuan in the first half, a third of the annual
investment quota. But the figure was 78.6 percent higher than for
the same period in 1997.
</P>
<P>
The number of mobile phone customers increased 2.5 million each
month of the second quarter, 680,000 more than the monthly figure
for the second quarter in 1997.
</P>
<P>
There are 27.5 telephones for every 100 urbanites now and 1.5
mobile phones on average.  
</P>
</TEXT>
