<HEADLINE> Chinese Listed Companies' Semi-Annual Reports </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The 800-some companies that are
listed on the Shanghai and Shenzhen stock markets began making
semi-annual performance reports on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Dalian Northeast Heating and Power Development Co. Ltd was the
first. The large thermal-power company reported net profits of 57
million yuan in the first half, up 105 percent from the same
period a year ago. Per share earnings averaged 0.538 yuan, an
increase of 58 percent.
