<HEADLINE> Hong Kong Stocks Close Higher </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong stocks rose 277.29
points, or 3.39 percent, to close at 8,456.22 Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
The market's turnover amounted to 4.637 billion HK dollars
(594.49 million U.S. dollars), 1.932 billion HK dollars (247.69
million U.S. dollars) more than that of Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Key Hang Seng Index gained 164.98 points, or 2.02 percent,
to open at 8,343.91 in the morning.
</P>
<P>
It rose 282.51 points, or 3.45 percent, to 8,461.44 at midday.
</P>
<P>
The Hong Kong share prices rose 79.73 points, or 0.98 percent,
to close at 8,178.93 Tuesday. 
</P>
