<HEADLINE> Soccer Fan Dies after Champs Elysee Crash </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, July 15 (Xinhua) -- One of the soccer fans hit by a car
on the Champs Elysee during World Cup celebrations early on Monday
has died, a hospital spokesman said on Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Around 80 revellers were injured when the car, driven by a
44-year old woman, ploughed into the crowds which had gathered in
the avenue after France's victory over Brazil.
</P>
<P>
The dead man, who was not named, was in his 40s. One radio
station reported that he was a Romanian.
</P>
<P>
Thirty-three people are still in hospital, ten of them still in
a serious condition.
</P>
<P>
The driver, who was a teacher, has been sent to a psychiatric
hospital. Police said she had been suffering psychiatric problems
for some time and was apparently panicked by the crowds.
</P>
<P>
Police estimated that nearly 1.5 million people poured into the
elegant, central avenue for a night of singing and dancing that
was probably the biggest outdoor celebration in the French capital
since Liberation Day in 1944. 
</P>
</TEXT>
