<HEADLINE> Mirages In Mysterious Chinese City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANTAI, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Two mirages that appeared on the
sea near the city of Penglai on China's Shandong Peninsula
recently represent the mystery of this place where gods have been
reported in Chinese legends.
</P>
<P>
Local people reported a foggy belt of lights with mountains and
cities alternatively appearing above them in the sky. The two
lasted about an hour, and then disappeared slowly.
</P>
<P>
Buildings, chimneys, towers, streets, and street lights could
all be seen, then the sky became clear again.
</P>
<P>
Several thousand tourists saw the mirages, and many more have
come to the city in recent days in hopes of seeing the phenomenon
again.
</P>
<P>
Penglai faces the Bohai and Huanghai seas and is known as a
dwelling place of the gods. There are records of many mirages in
local chronicles. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
