<HEADLINE> Iranian President Names New Interior Minister </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Iran's moderate President Mohammad
Khatami Wednesday named Vice President for Legal and Parliamentary
Affairs Seyed Abdolvahed Mousavi Lari as the new Interior
Minister.
</P>
<P>
Khatami made the nomination in a letter to Majlis (Parliament)
Speaker Ali Akbar Nateq-Nouri, which was read at the parliament's
open session Wednesday morning, the official news agency IRNA
reported.
</P>
<P>
Nateq-Nouri said that the Majlis would hold a vote of
confidence for Lari next Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
Though viewed also as one of Khatami's strong supporters, Lari
is expected to receive a vote of confidence from the
conservative-dominated Majlis, because he is more cautious than
the former Interior Minister Abdollah Nouri.
</P>
<P>
Nouri was impeached by the Majlis on June 21 in a no-confidence
vote for his radical views on carrying out liberal reforms in the
country. But Khatami soon appointed him vice president for
development and social affairs.
</P>
<P>
To be appointed, Lari will need a majority of votes in the
270-seat parliament.
</P>
<P>
Lari, 44, was twice elected Majlis members and appointed vice
president for legal and parliamentary affairs last August
following Khatami's election. 
</P>
</TEXT>
