<HEADLINE> Share Prices Inch Up on Singapore Stock Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Share prices inched up on the
Singapore Stock Market Wednesday as a strong overnight rally on
Wall Street, New York, and stable regional currencies lifted the
market sentiment.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Industrials Index (STII) gained
13.57 points to close at 1056.01 points.
</P>
<P>
However, dealers said the gains were unlikely to be sustained
as the underlying sentiment for the Singapore market remained weak
and uncertain ahead of further political developments in Japan.
</P>
<P>
The total market volume increased to 108.98 million shares
valued at 180.25 million Singapore dollars (about 106.66 million
U.S. dollars). Gainers outstripped losers by 229 to 75 while 287
stocks remained unchanged.
</P>
<P>
MBF Cap was the most active stock as it registered a turnover
of 7.09 million units. It was followed by TAC 200 which had 6.35
million shares done. SingTel was next with 4.42 million shares
changing hands.
</P>
<P>
Bukit Sem was the top gainer of the day as it gained 65 cents
to end at 8.10 Singapore dollars. Rothmans M edged up 50 cents to
finish at 11.90 Singapore dollars. Jurship inched up by 40 cents
to close at 8.00 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Tasek was the biggest loser as it lost 63
cents to finish at 1.35 Singapore dollars. Creative 50 fell by 50
cents to end at 21.10 Singapore dollars. 
</P>
</TEXT>
