<DOCNO> XIE19980715.0170 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Research Begun on Japan Bombing of Chongqing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHONGQING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- A group of Chinese historians
have been researching the bombing of Chongqing City during World
War II, an event which brought serious destruction to the city by
Japanese invaders in the 1940s.
</P>
<P>
Experts say that between 1938 and 1943, Japan bombed the
southwestern China city some 2,000 times, killing or injuring more
than 20,000 people and leaving over 60,000 buildings in ruins.
</P>
<P>
Many university students have volunteered to take part in the
research. They have visited survivors and collected a large amount
of written material along with more than 100 pictures.
</P>
<P>
Chongqing, the provisional capital after the fall of Nanjing
during the War of Resistance Against Japan (1937-1945), is now
China's newly established municipality directly under the central
government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980715.0171 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Construction Bank Leads In Housing Loans </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The China Construction Bank had
extended 172.9 billion yuan in real estate loans by the end of
June, with individual housing accounting for 26 billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
Bank sources say that in the first half of the year, the bank
added 35.1 billion yuan in housing development loans, or more than
one and a half times the amount for the same period last year, and
individual housing loans of 10.8 billion yuan, or almost 3 times
the amount for the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The bank has made an effort to work with the state's
"relatively comfortable housing project" and by the end of last
year, project loans had amounted to 14.3 billion yuan, or 93.4
percent of its total credit plan for the project. In 1997, it
provided 7.1 billion yuan for building 44.38 million sq.m. of
housing for the project.
</P>
<P>
A bank spokesman says that it has improved its operations and
simplified housing loan procedures, and provides new credit
services for individual housing.
</P>
<P>
This year the bank plans to increase its real estate loans by
50 billion yuan and individual housing loans by 3.5 billion yuan.
</P>
</TEXT>
