<HEADLINE> First Chinese Scenic Spots Receive Certificates </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua)-- Splendid China Miniature Scenic
Spots and China Folk Culture Villages have become the first two
tourist attractions in China to receive IS09002 certificates from
the International Standardization Organization.
</P>
<P>
These tourism "trump cards" of the Shenzhen Special Economic
Zone were granted the certificates for their nationally renowned
good service and management. Shenzhen, adjacent to Hong Kong, is
also a major tourist city of south China.
</P>
<P>
To further excel, the two scenic spots applied for the ISO9002
standard in August 1997, according to the "China Youth Daily."
In an effort to improve service, concrete measures concerning
worker responsibility and the service process are now in place.
</P>
<P>
For example, workers are required to patiently listen to
complaints from tourists and report them in a timely manner to
relevant authorities.
</P>
<P>
The toilet facilities in these scenic spots are another fine
example of standard service, providing users not only with soap
and toilet paper, but also with background music and decorative
potted plants. 
</P>
</TEXT>
