<HEADLINE> Jiaxing Development Zone To Be Satellite City Of Shanghai </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANGZHOU, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The Jiaxing Economic and
Technological Development Zone in east China's Zhejiang Province
is ready to become a satellite city of Shanghai to assist the
development of pillar industries in the largest industrial center
in China.
</P>
<P>
The zone, established six years ago, is 100 kilometers from
Shanghai and an hour's drive to Shanghai International
Airport. More than 600 industrial and commercial firms are located
in the zone, bringing in a total investment of six billion yuan
from abroad.
</P>
<P>
It has built 72 foreign-funded enterprises, 62 of which are
producers of metals, textiles, chemicals and building material.
</P>
<P>
To better serve pillar industries in Shanghai, the zone will
give priority to electronics, telecommunications, textiles,
machinery, pharmaceuticals and chemical development over the next
few years, said Zhao Youliu, vice mayor of Jiaxing.
</P>
<P>
Work on a high-tech park has started and construction of a
foodstuff processing center is well under way. At the same time,
renovation is underway at metal processing and textile facilities.
</P>
<P>
Under its development plan, the zone will approve 320
foreign-funded enterprises with an estimated overseas investment
of 2.5 billion U.S. dollars and raise its gross domestic product
to 8 billion yuan by 2010, when the zone expands its urban area to
13 sq. km. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
