<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Using Foreign Expertise To Expand Software Industry (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Carl Hsu, the president of Lucent
Technologies' Communications Software Business Group, says that
China badly needs management technology and expertise to
develop large scale software systems.
</P>
<P>
He says that although the country has the best software writers
in the world, most Chinese software companies have failed to
develop large software systems.
</P>
<P>
China now has more than 5,000 software companies, most of them
small. Total software sales in China amounted to 11 billion yuan
(1.3 billion US dollars) in 1997, with foreign products accounting
for 70 percent of that.
</P>
<P>
International software developers like Microsoft, IBM, and
Lucent are major suppliers of system software to the country's
transport, telecommunications, banking, and education sectors.
</P>
<P>
Hsu says that over the next three years Lucent, which is one of
the largest communications software suppliers in the world, will
put 200 million yuan into Beijing's Asia Pacific Communications
Software Regional Technology Center. Bell Labs set the center up
as part of a move to use foreign expertise to improve technology
in the software industry. The center will hire 200 local people to
develop large software systems.
</P>
<P>
China has designated the software industry as a pillar of the
economy and will direct resources into a Chinese operating system,
support systems, different software applications and the
government is sponsoring the first copyright software engineering
system to provide state-of-the-art tools for Chinese software
developers.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19980715.0187 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
