<HEADLINE> China Using Foreign Expertise To Expand Software Industry (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
China has set up software bases in Beijing, Shenyang, Jinan,
Chengdu, and Changsha.
</P>
<P>
The Founder Group, China's largest electronic publishing
company, has signed an agreement with IBM to develop
software.
</P>
<P>
China's largest PC manufacturer, the Legend Group, has begun to
install Windows on its computers, and Sweden's Erricsson has set
up a telecommunications research and development center in
Shanghai, while Lucent has set up Bell Labs institutes in Beijing
and Shanghai.
</P>
<P>
The Minister of Foreign Trade and Economic Cooperation Shi
Guangsheng says that China will pay equal attention to foreign
software and hardware, and to protect intellectual property
rights, China Software Association and the U.S.'s Business
Software Alliance are recommending authorized software.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Information Industry has also established a
nation-wide software registration system to regulate the software
market, and China has laws protecting software copyrights, like
the Regulation on Computer Software Protection. 
</P>
