<HEADLINE> Shandong to Enlarge Jinan Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, July 15 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province plans
to invest 800 million yuan for the enlargement of Jinan Airport to
hasten its economic development.
</P>
<P>
The current airport, located in the provincial capital of
Jinan, was built in 1992 and now serves 19 domestic and
overseas airlines.
</P>
<P>
The airport is expected to handle 500,000 passengers this year.
</P>
<P>
But with poor facilities, the airport fails to meet the
increasing demand for air transportation, and it is incapable of
handling large long-distance civil planes with full loads, said an
airport official.
</P>
<P>
The expansion projects include extending the current runway
from 2,600 m. to 3,600 m., and building a new parallel slide and
a 50,000-sq.-m. lounge.
</P>
<P>
When completed, the airport will be capable of handling three
million passengers and long-distance large and medium-sized planes
such as Boeing-747s and MD-11s.
</P>
<P>
The enlargement is now under way, according to the
official, who added that the new runway will be opened in October
1999. 
</P>
</TEXT>
