<HEADLINE> Bangladesh to Host D-8 Summit in November </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DHAKA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The Developing-Eight (D-8) Summit
comprising Bangladesh, Malaysia, Pakistan, Iran, Turkey, Egypt,
Nigeria and Indonesia will be held here on November 28-29 this
year, a Foreign Ministry official said here Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
To prepare for the second D-8 summit, a national preparatory
committee has been formed with Bangladeshi Foreign Minister Abdus
Samad Azad as the chairman.
</P>
<P>
Under the committee there will be four sub-committees: security
and traffic, media, finance and cultural affairs.
</P>
<P>
The D-8 was officially established in June 1997 with promoting
socio-economic development as its main objectives in accordance
with principles of peace, dialog, cooperation, justice, equality
and democracy.
</P>
<P>
Its first summit was held in Istanbul, Turkey in June last
year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
