<DOCNO> XIE19980715.0201 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China, U.S. Hold First Consultation on Maritime Military Safety </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The first Sino-U.S.
consultation on maritime military safety ended here today.
</P>
<P>
Both sides expressed satisfaction with the consultation and
believe it will promote mutual understanding and trust between the
two nations, while laying a foundation for resolving potential
maritime safety problems in the future.
</P>
<P>
This was the first such meeting since last January, when the
Sino-U.S. agreement establishing a consultation mechanism for
strengthening maritime military safety was signed.
</P>
<P>
Rear Admiral Zhao Guojun, deputy chief of staff of the Navy of
the People's Liberation Army of China, and Major General Earl
Hailstone, planning and policy officer of the U.S. Pacific
Command, jointly hosted the meeting.
</P>
<P>
Both sides exchanged views regarding laws and regulations
closely related to their respective maritime safety interests, and
those concerning their military activities at sea.
</P>
<P>
Zhao said he wishes to cooperate with the United States to
facilitate the flow of this exchange channel.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
