<HEADLINE> Iranian Guards Commander Vows to Protect World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Commander of the Iranian Islamic
Revolution's Guards Corps (IRGC) Yehya Rahim Safavi has said that
the IRGC would not only protect Iran, but also the Muslims
worldwide, the Iran Daily reported Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
"The IRGC intends to safeguard the Islamic Revolution (of
Iran)," Safavi said Tuesday during a visit to an IRGC battalion.
</P>
<P>
But he stressed that IRGC's duty "is not limited to Iran only,
it pertains to the entire Muslim population worldwide."
</P>
<P>
The IRGC belongs to the oppressed, and "wherever the voice of a
Muslim is raised, it will be responded to" by the force through
the orders of Iranian Supreme Leader Ayatollah Ali Khamenei, the
commander-in-chief of Iran's armed forces, he added.
</P>
<P>
Safavi's remarks have indicated that the IRGC holds on to the
policy of exporting Islamic revolution.
</P>
<P>
After Iranian President Mohammad Khatami, a moderate cleric,
came to power last August, the government has repeatedly stated
that Iran follows a policy of non-interference in other countries'
internal affairs and seeks ties with the rest of the world based
on mutual respect and mutual benefits.
</P>
<P>
The IRGC commander said the IRGC needed to be armed with "the
most advanced technology available."
</P>
<P>
"We should become more familiarized with modern know-how and
adhere to faith, in order to be able to fight against the
enemies." 
</P>
</TEXT>
