<HEADLINE> U.S. 3M Expanding Business in China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHANGHAI, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The 3M Company of the United
States says it hopes to have sales of one billion U.S. dollars in
China by the turn of this century.
</P>
<P>
The company set up 3M China Co. Ltd. in Shanghai in March 1985
as the first solely foreign-funded enterprise outside China's
first four special economic zones at Shenzhen, Zhuhai, Shantou and
Xiamen.
</P>
<P>
Over the past 13 years, 3M has built 180,000 sq.m. of workshops
in the Caohejing High-Tech Development Zone and Songjiang
Industrial Zone of Shanghai, employing 800 people to produce vinyl
electrical tape and reflector materials.
</P>
<P>
The company has offices in the cities of Beijing, Guangzhou and
Shenyang and has spent 100 million U.S. dollars on capital
construction.
</P>
<P>
It also set up a company in cooperation with the former
Ministry of Post and Telecommunications to produce
telecommunications products and started an international trading
company in Shanghai's Waigaoqiao Free Trade Zone this April.
</P>
<P>
3M's China sales were worth about 100 million U.S. dollars last
year, according to company sources. 
</P>
</TEXT>
