<HEADLINE> Economic and Trade Fair Opens In South China City </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The Sixth Guangzhou Fair, an
economic and trade fair held annually since 1993, opened today in
this capital city of south China's Guangdong Province. The fair
will run through July 20.
</P>
<P>
Attending the activities are enterprises from the ROK, Canada,
Thailand, New Zealand, Vietnam, as well as Hong Kong, Macao, and
domestic provinces such as Anhui, Hebei, Guangdong, Zhejiang and
Jiangsu.
</P>
<P>
More than 1,100 domestic economic and technological cooperative
entities are participating in the fair, seeking to attract
domestic as well as overseas investors from 20 countries and
regions including Malaysia and France.
</P>
<P>
Seventy-six enterprises from the ROK are showcasing their
name-brand products for daily use and their the-state-of-the-art
scientific and technological items.
</P>
<P>
In addition to products, 26 companies from Hong Kong are
presenting network services for electronic businesses.
</P>
<P>
More than 80 enterprises from the Guangzhou Economic and
Technological Development Zone are displaying more than 400
products, and are the first group of representatives from the zone
to attend a fair of this kind.
</P>
<P>
Trade volume conducted during the past five fairs amounted to
5.06 billion yuan, and the number of contracts signed reached 396,
involving nearly 32.8 billion yuan in total investment, including
nearly 2.3 billion U.S. dollars of overseas investment. 
</P>
