<HEADLINE> Chinese Foreign Minister Meets Arafat </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Chinese Foreign Minister Tang
Jiaxuan said today that China will use every opportunity and join
the international community in contributing to the promotion of an
early realization of a comprehensive, just and lasting peace in
the Middle East.
</P>
<P>
Tang made the remark this morning at a meeting with
visiting President of the State of Palestine Yasser Arafat.
</P>
<P>
Reiterating China's principled stance on the Mideast issue,
Tang said that China's position of supporting the just cause of
the Palestinian people will not change no matter how the
international situation evolves.
</P>
<P>
Quoting an ancient Chinese saying that "A just cause gains
abundant support", Tang expressed the conviction that the
Palestinian people's cause will succeed.
</P>
<P>
Tang again expressed congratulations on the upgrading of the status
of the Palestinian representation to the United Nations, and the
recent resolution passed by the U.N. supporting the Palestinian
people on the Jerusalem issue.
</P>
<P>
He noted that China holds that relevant U.N. resolutions and the
"Land for Peace" principle are the basis for the Mideast talks,
and breaking the stalemate at an early date is in the interests of
all parties concerned.
</P>
<P>
Arafat briefed Tang on the Mideast peace talks and Palestine's
current difficulties, and hoped that the international community
can exert greater effort to promote peace and help the peace
process out of its current deadlock.
</P>
<P>
Arafat expressed his appreciation for China's consistent
support for the just cause of the Palestinian people in past
years, and China's powerful support for Palestine in all
international arenas including the U.N..
</P>
<P>
He also spoke highly of a principled China and its unremitting
efforts to push forward the peace process, and hoped that as a
permanent member of the U.N. Security Council, China can play a
more active and effective role in promoting the peace
process. 
</P>
</TEXT>
