<BODY>
<HEADLINE> East China Province Importing Water-Efficient Irrigation Equipment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, July 15 (Xinhua) -- East China's Shandong Province,
which is badly in need of water, plans to import water-efficient
irrigation equipment from overseas over the next three years.
</P>
<P>
The province has only 357 cubic meters per capita of water
resources, less than a sixth of the nation's average and far less
than the international standards of 1,000 cubic meters per capita.
</P>
<P>
The drying-up of the Yellow River and the increasing use of
water for economic development have worsened the situation, so, the
province will spend nearly 3 billion yuan annually over the next
three years developing some 333,000 hectares of irrigated farmland
using the new equipment.
</P>
<P>
In recent years, the province has made a great effort to use
water-efficient irrigation methods and has more than 3.33 million
hectares of farmland irrigated this way.
</P>
<P>
Since last year, it has imported irrigation equipment from
France, Austria, and Israel. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
