<HEADLINE> Manufacturing Sector Registers Decline in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Both production and sales in the
country's manufacturing sector showed decreases for April 1998
compared to their year-ago levels, the National Statistics Office
said Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
A survey released from the office showed value of production
dipped by 2.0 percent and volume of production, by 11.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
Value for sales slightly increased by 0.7 percent while sales
volume declined by 9.9 percent, it showed.
</P>
<P>
On a month-on-month basis, value and volume of sales decreased
by 1.1 percent and 3.7 percent, respectively, after posting
increases in the past three months.
</P>
<P>
Value and volume of production likewise declined by 6.6 percent
and 6.7 percent, respectively, according to the survey.
</P>
<P>
It also showed that declines in both production and sales of
basic metals, petroleum, transport equipment and textiles
contributed significantly to the bad performance of the
manufacturing sector in April 1998. 
</P>
</TEXT>
