<HEADLINE> Forest Tourism In Northern Chinese Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TAIYUAN, July 15 (Xinhua) -- North China's Shanxi Province has
developed its forest tourism rapidly and expects it to become a
new local economic growth area.
</P>
<P>
The province began the lucrative businesses in 1992 and now has
360,000 hectares of forest reserves and ranks 4th in the country
both in forest reserve acreage.
</P>
<P>
