<HEADLINE> Fuel Tanker Explosion Kills 10 People in Kenya </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Ten people, including a pregnant
woman, were burnt to death in southwestern Kenya Monday night
when an overturned petrol tanker burst into flames as villagers
scrambled for the liquid.
</P>
<P>
More than 50 others suffered serious burns in Siaya District,
Nyanza Province, local media reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The tanker overturned after a tire burst at about 7:00 p.m..
The Daily Nation newspaper quoted eyewitnesses as saying that the
fire was started after one of the onlookers struck a match,
apparently trying to light a cigarette as the villagers scrambled
for leaking fuel.
</P>
<P>
On Tuesday morning, the tanker was still burning, with five
bodies lying next to it.
</P>
<P>
Sources in Nairobi said that the tanker belonged to the Total
Uganda Company. The tanker's loader and driver were not hurt.
</P>
<P>
The tanker had reportedly drawn the petrol at the Kisumu depot
of the Kenya Oil Pipeline and was heading for Ugandan capital
Kampala when the accident occurred.  
</P>
