<HEADLINE> Major News Items in Leading S. African Newspapers </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The following are major news
items in leading South African newspapers Wednesday:
</P>
<P>
The Citizen:
</P>
<P>
-- A general ban on the carrying of weapons at political
meetings or any other political events will apply throughout the
election campaign leading to the 1999 general elections in South
Africa.
</P>
<P>
Business Day:
</P>
<P>
-- European Union and South African negotiating teams on a
free trade agreement between the two regions were locked in
negotiations in Pretoria until late Tuesday night in a bid to
thrash out the last remaining hitches in the way of an agreement.
</P>
