<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Eastern Han Dynasty Tombs Excavated in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Pottery models of toilets,
buildings, stoves and storage areas have been unearthed from ten
tombs dating back to the Eastern Han Dynasty (25-220) in Beijing's
suburban Miyun county.
</P>
<P>
The models served as netherworld living facilities for the
dead. During the Eastern Han Dynasty, it was believed that people
in the netherworld lived in the same way as they did in this world.
</P>
<P>
The models were found among nearly 100 relics unearthed from
some ten tombs located within an area of 1.33 hectares.
</P>
<P>
Other relics include coins and pottery animal figures and
vessels.
</P>
<P>
Chinese archaeologists believe the find will contribute to the
study of the history of Beijing. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
