<HEADLINE> El Guerrouj Improves Morceli's World Record </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Morocco's Hicham El Guerrouj improved
the world 1500 meters record when he clocked an astonishing three
minutes 26.00 seconds at the Golden Gala athletics meeting in Rome
on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
El Guerrouj clipped more than a second off the listed world
mark of 3:27.37 set by Algerian mentor Noureddine Morceli in Nice
three years ago.
</P>
<P>
The Moroccan said: "I came here with the idea of breaking the
record. I ran 3:33 here in pouring rain last year. This time the
weather was perfect."
</P>
<P>
American world champion Marion Jones powered to her second
consecutive Golden League victory over 100 meters to remain on
target for an IAAF jackpot of one million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
Jones produced her best performance of the season to win the
event in 10.75 seconds, seven hundredths faster than her time in
Oslo last week.
</P>
<P>
Compatriot Chrystie Gaines finished second in 11.00 seconds
with Savatheda Fynes of the Bahamas came third in 11.02.
</P>
<P>
Namibia's Frankie Fredericks beat other rivals to win the men's
100m race in 9.97 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Trinidad-Tobago's Ato Boldon came second in 9.99 and world
champion Maurice Greene was third in 10.04.
</P>
<P>
World and Olympic 400m champion Michael Johnson bounced back
from his disappointing showing in Oslo to win in 44.40 seconds
ahead of Britian's Mark Richardson in 44.62 and American Tyree
Washington in 44.71. 
</P>
</TEXT>
