<HEADLINE> Shanghai Offers 600 Million Yuan to Support High-Tech Ventures </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The Shanghai municipal government
has decided to offer 600 million yuan (72 million U.S. dollars) to
support the establishment of more high-tech ventures in China's
leading industrial city.
</P>
<P>
Sources from the Ministry of Science and Technology said this
large amount of money will be used to guarantee inter-bank loans,
stock investments and loan discounts.
</P>
<P>
A special agency is expected to be established soon in Shanghai
to appraise market prospects and investment risks for the
soon-to-be-established high-tech ventures.
</P>
<P>
The appraisal programs will enjoy a series of preferential
policies in obtaining discounted loans and the reduction of various
taxes.
</P>
<P>
According to a new regulation adopted recently by the Shanghai
municipal government, the city will establish a center for
encouraging the industrialization of scientific achievements.
</P>
<P>
The 18-item regulation also stipulates that the patent-holders
of these scientific achievements will be allowed to use their
inventions as intangible-assets investments in the high-tech
ventures.
</P>
<P>
An inventor can thus hold as high as 35 percent of the shares
of a venture.
</P>
<P>
Confirmed high-tech ventures will also enjoy several reduced
charges and a reduction of taxes over a specified period of time.
</P>
<P>
A special award is also expected to be conferred regularly on
outstanding scientists who bring their achievements to Shanghai for
industrialization.  
</P>
</TEXT>
