<HEADLINE> Chinese President Meets With British Duke Of Gloucester </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- President Jiang Zemin expressed
the hope today that China and Britain would continue their efforts
to elevate bilateral exchange and cooperation in various areas to
a new level.
</P>
<P>
He said it is the common aspiration of the people of both China
and Britain, both influential nations in the world, and in line
with their interests, to intensify bilateral cooperation in all
fields.
</P>
<P>
During a meeting with visiting British Duke and Duchess of
Gloucester and their party here this morning, President Jiang
highly appraised the contributions made by the British royal
family to the development of Sino-British ties.
</P>
<P>
The successful China visit by Queen Elizabeth II in 1986 had
pushed forward bilateral relations of the two countries and the
smooth transfer of power in Hong Kong last year had opened up a
new chapter in the annals of Sino-British ties, Jiang said, adding
that the current China tour by Duke and Duchess of Gloucester
would also produce a positive impact on the further growth of
these ties.
</P>
<P>
Duke of Gloucester said he was happy to come to visit China. He
spoke highly of China's economic growth and the development of
Britain-China relations. The Duke also conveyed to President Jiang
the greetings from Queen Elizabeth II.
</P>
<P>
President Jiang, too, asked the Duke to forward his greetings
to the British Queen.
</P>
<P>
The Duke and Duchess of Gloucester are here on a visit to China
at the invitation of the Chinese People's Institute of Foreign
Affairs. 
</P>
</TEXT>
