<HEADLINE> Russia Condemns Trend of Fascism </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 14 (Xinhua) -- The Russian president's Human
Rights Committee has strongly condemned the trend of increasingly
rampant fascism and racism in Russia.
</P>
<P>
Russian fascist groups have been behind conflicts between
different races, ethnic groups and religions, and more and more
militarized extremist organizations advocate racial superiority
and national exclusionism publicly, conducting terrorist
activities at other races.
</P>
<P>
The statement attributed the trend to growing serious social
problems of unemployment, sharp contrasts between different social
classes and rampant crime.
</P>
<P>
The statement said that laws should be perfected to crackdown
on the activities of racists and fascists.
</P>
<P>
President Boris Yeltsin said in a speech, broadcast to remember
the Great Patriotic War recently ,that the Second World war
started by the fascists should not be repeated. 
</P>
