<HEADLINE> Russia Prepared to Mediate on Drozdy Row </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Russia is willing to mediate
between Belarus and the western countries about their dispute over
embassies in the Drozdy compound, a Russian foreign ministry
official said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Extreme actions and the isolation of Belarus would not do any
good, Vladimir Rakhmanin, a spokesman of the Foreign Ministry was
quoted by the ITAR-TASS news agency as saying.
</P>
<P>
Russia advocates a solution which is mutually satisfactory and
in line with the Vienna Convention, Rakhmanin said.
</P>
<P>
Rakhmanin said he hoped the Belarussian side could take
concrete steps in this regard.
</P>
<P>
In late April, Belarus asked foreign missions living in the
Drozdy compound to vacate, saying it was a necessity to begin the
overhaul of the old building. All diplomats of the European Union
refused and were later recalled home.
</P>
<P>
Despite compromising signals from the Belarussian side, the EU
imposed a visa ban on all Belarussian officials on July 10.
</P>
<P>
On July 13 Belarussian President Alexandr Lukashenko wrote to
the Foreign Minister of Austria, the Rotating Presidency of the
EU, reiterating Belarus' call for negotiations to end the crisis.
</P>
</TEXT>
