<HEADLINE> Hungary Praises China's Role in Promoting Peace </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Hungarian military leader Vegh
Ferene said Tuesday that China will play an important role in
promoting world peace and stability in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Ferene, Commander and Chief of General Staff of the Hungary
National Defensce Forces, was speaking at a meeting with a visiting
group of the Chinese People's Liberation Army led by Xu Caihou,
Political Commissar of the PLA Jinan Region.
</P>
<P>
Ferene praised China's economic achievements in recent years.
Emphasizing China's political, economic and military influence, he
said China would play a very important role in maitaining world
peace and stability in the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
He also spoke highly of China's decision to keep RMB from
depreciating, which was critical for Asia's financial stability in
the current economic crisis.
</P>
<P>
Ferene said he was happy with the development of
Sino-U.S. relations, which was promoted by the successful meeting
between leaders of the two countries.
</P>
<P>
Ferene noted that the new Hungarian government would not change
its foreign policies, including its policy towards China. Hungary
attached great importance to the development of friendly relations
with China, including military relations, he said.
</P>
<P>
Before meeting with Ferene, the PLA delegation, which began its
visit on July 12, and is due to leave on July 17, visited
Hungary's Army and Air Force and some military academies. 
</P>
