<HEADLINE> Italian, Eritrean FMs Meet on Crisis with Ethiopia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Italian Foreign Minister Lamberto
Dini met with his Eritrean counterpart Haile Woldetensae here on
Thursday to discuss the crisis between Ethiopia and Eritrea.
</P>
<P>
The Italian Foreign Ministry said the meeting with the Eritrean
minister followed a July 9 meeting here between Dini and Ethiopian
Foreign Minister Scyoum Mesfin.
</P>
<P>
Dini told Woldetensae that Italy continued to follow the
situation between the two countries attentively and with much
concern.
</P>
<P>
He called for an end to all hostilities and pressed for a
peaceful solution to the controversy, emphasizing the negative
effect that the conflict was having on the entire Horn of Africa.
</P>
<P>
Dini stressed that Italy was committed to a solution within the
framework of United Nations Resolution 1177, which includes
operations to define the border between the two countries, and
backed the peace plan made by the Organization for African Unity.
</P>
<P>
Dini urged both sides to stop the arrest and expulsion of
citizens who happened to live on the wrong side of the border.
</P>
<P>
Responsible behavior would help ease tensions in the region and
promote the peace negotiations supported by the Organization for
African Unity, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
