<HEADLINE> Public Burying Grounds to Be Rectified </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Blaring irregularities in the
management of public burial grounds have prompted the central
government to launch a nationwide rectification campaign.
</P>
<P>
The General Office of the State Council recently released a
Ministry of Civil Affairs circular stipulating the closure of all
cemeteries built without local government approval.
</P>
<P>
The circular prohibits public burial grounds from allowing
rituals involving superstition.
</P>
<P>
The circular also prohibits illegal sales of graves and
masoleum niches. It instructs all cemetery administrations to
exert total control over space in graveyards. 
</P>
</TEXT>
