<HEADLINE> Shenzhen Airport Ready to Help HK </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN July 15 (Xinhua) -- Shenzhen Airport is fully prepared
to assist neighboring Hong Kong's new airport at Chek Lap Kok in
its cargo transportation, the "China Daily" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen Airport was authorized by the Civil Air Administration
of China (CAAC) early yesterday morning to handle some cargo
transportation for Chek Lap Kok airport upon airline companies'
request, said officials at Shenzhen Airport.
</P>
<P>
Problems with cargo transportation have been reported at the
new airport at Chek Lap Kok.
</P>
<P>
The CAAC notice came after the Hong Kong airport authorities
asked the central government for rights to land some of its cargo
planes at Shenzhen Airport at Huangtian.
</P>
<P>
Various departments of Shenzhen's entry ports have established
a command post and are working together around-the-clock to
guarantee operations, logistics and safety at the airport.
</P>
<P>
Officials at Shenzhen Airport said that it can offer service to
more than 20 cargo planes or 1,000 to 2,000 tons of cargo every
day.
</P>
<P>
Shenzhen Airport has an annual cargo handling capacity of about
250,000 tons, ranking sixth among China's airports, while it
processes about 100,000 tons of cargo every year at present,
leaving much room for additional business. 
</P>
</TEXT>
