<HEADLINE> Polluted Water Kills 7 People in Brazil </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
RIO DE JANEIRO, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Polluted water in the
northeastern Brazilian state of Bahia has already caused the death
of 7 people and intoxication of 80 others in the last 20 days,
local press reported on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The incident, which happened mainly in the southern part of the
state and in the city of Santa Luzia, some 560 kilometers from the
state capital of Salvador de Bahia, was due to the spread of
cholera virus.
</P>
<P>
Close to 80 people were hospitalized after they drank water
contaminated with cholera and other toxic microorganisms, the
reports said.
</P>
<P>
Experts have decided that eight different water sources were
unsuitable for human consumption.
</P>
<P>
Santa Luzia officials said the situation is under control.
Local citizens were advised to boil water before drinking and to
take measures to prevent the virus from spreading further.
</P>
