<DOCNO> XIE19980715.0270 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-07-15 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Poverty on Rise in Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Italy witnessed an increase of
families living below the poverty line last year, said a report
released by a ministerial commission on social affair Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The report said that in 1997, a total of 2.245 million
families' expenditures on consumer goods and services were less
than the national average. The number of impoverished households
rose by 166,000 compared with that of 1996.
</P>
<P>
It said that 71 percent of poor families live in the
under-developed southern region whose population occupied only 36
percent of the country's total.
</P>
<P>
While the families with more than five members were more at
risk than others, the report added, the percentage of poor single
person was also on the rise, up from 9 percent in 1996 to 11.6
percent in 1997. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
