<HEADLINE> Ecuadorian Exports to Community of Andean Nations Increase </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
QUITO, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Ecuadorian exports to countries of
the Community of Andean Nations (CAN) increased by six percent
during the first five months this year compared with the same
period in 1997, official figures released on Tuesday showed.
</P>
<P>
A report by Ecuador's Central Bank said that Ecuadorian exports
went up from 241.6 million U.S. dollars between January and May
last year to 256 million dollars in the same period in 1998.
</P>
<P>
Exports to Bolivia, Venezuela and Peru increased while exports
to Colombia fell by 7.4 percent.
</P>
<P>
In 1997, Ecuadorian exports to CAN totalled 636 million
dollars, according to official data.
</P>
<P>
The Ecuadorian government hopes that bilateral trade with Peru
will increase once both countries sign a peace agreement that will
end their border dispute. 
</P>
</TEXT>
