<HEADLINE> Deadly Dengue Spreads in Costa Rica </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SAN JOSE, July 14 (Xinhua) -- At least 18 cases of hemorrhagic
dengue have been detected in the southern zone of Costa Rica, the
Health Ministry said Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Eduardo Sanchez, director of the Hospital de Golfito said
there were about 50 dengue cases discovered everyday, most of them
very serious, but not of the hemorrhagic type which is particularly
deadly.
</P>
<P>
Health Minister Rogelio Pardo started a regional tour on
Tuesday to organize a prevention and attention program.
</P>
<P>
Dengue is an epidemic disease in the region, which erupted in
1993, but is now worse than before.
</P>
<P>
The disease is transmitted by the Aedes Aegypti mosquito. It
causes high fever and body and head aches, and even death.
</P>
<P>
The authorities have intensified the educational campaign to
control the outbreak and prevent its spreading to other zones in
the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
