<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, July 15 (Xinhua) -- Subscribers to the public data
network in China have increased at an annual rate of 100 percent
over the past four years, with the number reaching 820,000 by
the end of last May, "China Securities" reported today.
</P>
<P>
Data network services will maintain high-speed growth in the
upcoming years, said Zuo Fengjie, deputy director of the State
Data Telecommunications Bureau.
</P>
