<HEADLINE> Guangdong Has Fast Population Growth Rate </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, July 15 (Xinhua) -- China's Guangdong Province had
an increase of 7.05 million people over the past seven years, to
a total of 70.5 million at the end of last year.
</P>
<P>
The population grew at a rate of 11.5 per 1,000 people, 2.77
percentage point higher than the national average. At such a pace,
experts say, Guangdong will be very much likely to outnumber
Jiangsu as the fourth largest province by 1999.
</P>
<P>
Experts attribute the growth rate to uncontrolled births in
some of its rural areas.
</P>
<P>
This has become harder now for Guangdong to keep its
population growth target below 73.7 million by the end
of the century, experts say, and warn that the province needs to
encourage family planning more.
</P>
<P>
According to designed target, Guangdong should keep its birth
rate within 15 per 1,000 people and natural population growth rate
under 10 per 1,000 people a year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
