<HEADLINE> Indonesia Sets Aside 300M Dollars as Food Subsidies </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, July 15 (Xinhua) -- The Indonesian government has
earmarked 4.5 trillion rupiah (300 million U.S. dollars) as
subsidies to cope with the food shortage after the economic
meltdown, a senior official said.
</P>
<P>
