a special market operation program launched to provide assistance
to 7.3 million poor families all over the country in the form of
rice sales at 1,000 rupiah per kilogram.
</P>
<P>
In the markets, the price of rice has increased to more than
3,000 rupiah per kilogram.
</P>
<P>
The production of rice in the country was predicted to drop by
6.3 percent compared with that of last year, so the government has
decided to import 3.1 million tons of rice this year.
</P>
<P>
In addition, Saefuddin said, the government would also provide
4 trillion rupiah in fuel oil subsidy, bringing the total
subsidies to 8.5 trillion rupiah (560 million U.S. dollars).
</P>
