<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, July 15 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS -- China on Tuesday strongly urged Nicaragua and
the other countries to stop immediately their illegal activities
of interfering in China's internal affairs.
</P>
<P>
In a letter on July 8, 1998 to the Secretary-General of the
United Nations, Qin Huasun, Chinese Permanent Representative to
the United Nations, said, Nicaragua and a very small number of
other countries once again put the so-called "Taiwan's
representation at the United Nations" before the General Assembly.
</P>
<P>
Ambassador Qin said the brazen attempt was to challenge the
General Assembly Resolution 2758, create "two Chinas" or "one
China, one Taiwan" at the United Nations and split a sovereign
state.
</P>
<P>
Qin stressed such illegal activities have severely contravened
the purposes and principles of the Charter of the United Nations,
seriously encroached upon China's sovereignty and territorial
integrity and grossly interfered in its internal affairs.
(UN-China-Taiwan)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
ABU DHABI -- Six bodies of the Ukrainian cargo plane that
plunged into the sea on Monday night soon after take-off from the
United Arab Emirates have been recovered by the coastal and border
guards.
</P>
<P>
The remaining two of the eight crew members on board the plane
when it crashed were still missing and feared dead. The search was
continuing for them and the instruments that recorded flight
condition and data.
</P>
<P>
The tragic incident took place Monday soon after the Ilyushin
76, leased by a Kiev-based private air company, took off for
Mykolayiv, Ukraine. The plane crashed about 500 meters offshore.
(UAE-Ukraine-Plane Crash)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- Indian Defense Minister George Fernandes on
Tuesday turned down Pakistan's demand for a plebiscite in Jammu
and Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
Talking to newsmen here, Fernandes argued that it was too late
to discuss the question of a plebiscite.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, Pakistan High Commissioner to India Ashraf Jehangir
Qazi said in a newspaper interview here that Jammu and Kashmir is
an indivisible state which is neither part of India nor Pakistan.
He reiterated Pakistan's stand to carry out the 1948 U.N.
Resolution on Kashmir which referred to a plebiscite on the issue.
(India-Pakistan-Kashmir)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. President Bill Clinton Tuesday called for
urgent action on solution to the 2000 computer problem Y2K and
urged federal agencies and all American businesses to have their
Y2K remedies ready by next March.
</P>
<P>
In a speech at the National Academy of Sciences, the president
said, "because the difficulty is as far-flung as the billions of
microchips that run everything from farm equipment to VCRs, this
is not a challenge that is susceptible to a single government
program or an easy fix."
</P>
<P>
He said he has ordered all agencies to have their Y2K remedies
ready by next March. He also noted that many big corporations are
moving swiftly to prepare themselves, but in spite of all this
progress in the business sector just as in the government sector,
there are still gaping holes. (US-Clinton-Y2K Problem)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
LUANDA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Leaders of Angola, Namibia and
Democratic Congo held a summit here Tuesday, urging Angola's
rebel UNITA forces to stick to the peace deal agreed upon
"unconditionally."
</P>
<P>
A joint communique to this effect was issued after Angolan
President Jose Eduardo dos Santos, Namibian President Sam Nujoma
and President of the Democratic Republic of Congo (DRC) Laurent
Kabila met and held a tripartite summit on Angola's peace here.
</P>
<P>
The statement analyzed the situation in Angola and urged Jonas
Savimbi, Chairman of the National Union for Total Independence of
Angola (UNITA) to put an end to all its military actions,
cooperate with the other side in the peace process, and disarm
its military men. (Angola-Tripartite Summit) 
</P>
</TEXT>
