<HEADLINE> Colombian-Peruvian Trade drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTAFE DE BOGOTA, July 14 (Xinhua) -- Trade between Colombia
and Peru amounted to 220 billion pesos (162 million U.S. dollars)
in the first three months of 1998, a 20 percent reduction over the
same period last year.
</P>
<P>
A report by Colombia's Proexport said Tuesday that in the
January to March period, Peruvian exports to Colombia were 37
million dollars. The bilateral trade was 766.8 million dollars
last year.
</P>
<P>
Peru is an important trade partner for Colombia within the
Andean Community, which groups Venezuela, Ecuador and
Bolivia. 
</P>
